          <head/>
          <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85006343">
            <summary>1 copy of Maqāmāt al-Ḥarīrī by al-Ḥarīrī</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="ar" otherLangs="fa">Arabic &amp; Persian</textLang>
            <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_RSPA_111-item1">
              <locus from="1v" to="297r"/>
              <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21224">Maqāmāt al-Ḥarīrī</title>
              <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_21224">مقامات الحريري</title>
              <note><p>Copied for William Jones by Ḥājj ʿAbd Allāh al-Makkī.</p></note>
              <incipit xml:lang="ar">بسم الله الرحمن الرحيم. اللهم إنا نحمدك على ما علمت من البيان
                والهمت من التبيان</incipit>
              <explicit xml:lang="ar">يحظي بالعفو إنه هو أهل التقوى وأهل المغفرة وولي الخيرات في
                الدنيا والآخرة</explicit>
              <colophon>وكان الفراغ من تسطير هذا الكتاب بعون الملك الوهاب يوم الأحد المبارك لاثنين
                وعشرين خلين من شهر رمضان سنة ألف ومايتين وأربع من الهجرة المحمدية وذلك بأمر عالي
                الرتب والمفاخر كابرا عن حضرة المخدوم سر وليم يونس الذي هو أحد حكام العدالة العالية
                السلطانية بدار الأمارة كلكتة المحمية على يد الخادم حاج الحرمين الشريفين الحاج عبد
                الله المكي ولله در القايل. أقشم بالبيت وأياته *** ومشعر الحج وميقاته. إن الحريري حري
                بأن *** تكتب بالتبر مقاماته</colophon>
              <decoNote/>
              <author><persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc"
                  key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164659053.0x000001 viaf_9907600"
                  >al-Ḥarīrī</persName><persName xml:lang="ar" key="viaf_9907600"
                >الحريري</persName></author>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
          <physDesc>
            <objectDesc form="codex">
              <supportDesc material="chart">
                <support>Strong European paper, barely damaged, with Taylor, GR, fleur de lys water
                  marks.</support>
                <extent>ff.- iii+297+iv <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                    <height>320</height>
                    <width>200</width>
                  </dimensions><dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                    <height>200</height>
                    <width>110</width>
                  </dimensions></extent>
                <foliation><p>European numerals in pencil.</p></foliation>
                <condition><p>Textblock in excellent condition – the paper has sustained little
                    damage, beyond the large rip on f99. However, the binding has completely broken
                    apart and is no longer attached to the textblock. The text therefore cracks at
                    f99 along the spine, almost pulling apart.</p></condition>
              </supportDesc>
              <layoutDesc>
                <layout columns="1" writtenLines="9"><p>Uniform layout of nine lines per column per
                    page.</p></layout>
              </layoutDesc>
            </objectDesc>
            <handDesc hands="1">
              <summary>Black ink thuluth script of <persName key="person_f8177" role="scr">Ḥājj ʿAbd
                  Allāh al-Makkī</persName></summary>
              <handNote script="Arabic" scope="major"/>
            </handDesc>
            <decoDesc>
              <decoNote><p/></decoNote>
            </decoDesc>
            <additions><p>Only occasional annotations by Jones (metres of poems, for example on
                f200v). Other annotations by him include “fine” or curly brackets next to certain
                verses for highlighting. On f1r he has written “The Moral Discourses of Harīrī who
                was born at Basra yc 1054”. Throughout there are Arabic and Persian glosses in a
                minute hand, that of Abdallah al-Makki, which serve to explain the complex words and
                meanings of the maqāmāt</p></additions>
            <bindingDesc>
              <p>Brown leather and board binding with floral (European style Indian) desin in gilded
                frieze with marbled endpapers. Same cover as some of Jones' collection Fatāwā
                ʿĀlamgīrī.</p>
            </bindingDesc>
            <accMat><p/></accMat>
          </physDesc>
          <history>
            <origin calendar="Hijri-qamari" when="1790-06-04" when-custom="21_Ramaḍān_1204"
